57420523.title: List of AMD Ryzen processors
57420523.extract: The Ryzen family is an x86-64 microprocessor family from AMD, based on the Zen microarchitecture. The Ryzen lineup includes Ryzen 3, Ryzen 5, Ryzen 7, Ryzen 9, and Ryzen Threadripper with up to 96 cores. All consumer desktop Ryzens (except PRO models) and all mobile processors with the HX suffix have an unlocked multiplier. In addition, all support Simultaneous Multithreading (SMT) except earlier Zen/Zen+ based desktop and mobile Ryzen 3, and some models of Zen 2 based mobile Ryzen.
